title: Static Analysis

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE.description: Allows an application to read from external storage.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.CHANGE_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows applications to change network connectivity state.

android.permission.USE_BIOMETRIC.description: Allows an app to use device supported biometric modalities.

android.permission.USE_FINGERPRINT.description: This constant was deprecated in API level 28. Applications should request USE_BIOMETRIC instead

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE.description: Allows a regular application to use Service.startForeground

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Permission for cloud to device messaging.

manifest_analysis.title:
Broadcast Receiver (com.google.firebase.iid.FirebaseInstanceIdReceiver) is Protected by a permission, but the protection level of the permission should be checked.
Permission: com.google.android.c2dm.permission.SEND
[android:exported=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: A Broadcast Receiver is found to be shared with other apps on the device therefore leaving it accessible to any other application on the device. It is protected by a permission which is not defined in the analysed application. As a result, the protection level of the permission should be checked where it is defined. If it is set to normal or dangerous, a malicious application can request and obtain the permission and interact with the component. If it is set to signature, only applications signed with the same certificate can obtain the permission.
manifest_analysis.name: is Protected by a permission, but the protection level of the permission should be checked.[android:exported=true]

- More space for Market and History lists on Exchange. Just scroll down and Tokens list will take over the entire screen. It’s beautiful.
- Fixed rare bug, that is so rare even we didn’t know about it. Until recently. So now we fixed it. (It had to do with transactions failing to sign.)
- Fixed ‘From' account name bug
- Peggy the astronaut is waiting for you once you create your new wallet, instead of popping up out of nowhere on you.
- Disable the buy button if it's pressed once, so you don’t end up starting multiple purchases all at once.
- Improved UI smoothness.
- We now hide ‘Advanced Features’ and Settings items if you
- Show “<0.000001” instead of 0.000000000000000132728116 if the amount is really low. To keep you sane, and to keep our UI from blowing up.
- We now properly handle and display ‘dropped’ transactions
- Fiat prices are now updated more frequently on Swap screen.
- Fixed Send input field jumping behavior in some rare cases.
- More accurate fee estimates in Buy Ether flow
- Fix ETH input on Custom Amount screen in Buy Ether
- We now use custom numeric keyboard instead of a system keyboard for PIN entry. There’re two reasons: it’s more secure, and it always works, on all devices, unlike native system keyboards (!).
- Recalculate max input if user change fee type in Send, so you can actually send it.
- Exchange UI fixes
- Added a card shadow on Swap Tokens screen.
- Fixed the Swap button if token's info screen is opened from market search
- Fixed the value's suffix on token info screen
- Fixed some crashes

### Release 1.1.1 (197)

- More accurate price estimates for low liquidity token swaps
- More accurate transaction fee estimates
- More clear wallet restore process when restoring a wallet with multiple accounts in it
- Improved connection to MEW website via MEWconnect protocol
- Multiple other fixes and improvements.

### Release 1.1.0 (163)

- Exchange and swap: swap tokens between one another, MEW will search multiple DEXs to find the best price for you. 
- Better handling of large fonts
- Fixes to connection issues when connecting to MEW web
- Custom, more secure keyboard for PIN entry
- Total portfolio value at the top of your wallet
- Multiple other fixes and improvements.

"market_item_description_text" : "Эфириум был запущен в 2015 году и является лидирующим программируемым блокчейном в мире.
 Как и другие блокчейны, Эфириум имеет собственную криптовалюту — Эфир (ETH). ETH это цифровые деньги. Если вы слышали о биткоине, ETH обладает многими похожими свойствами. Он полностью цифровой, и его можно мгновенно послать любому человеку в мире. Создание ETH не контролируется каким-либо правительством или компанией. Это происходит децентрализованно, и ETH – дефицитный товар. Люди во всем мире пользуются ETH для оплаты товаров или услуг, как средство сбережения или в качестве залога.
 Но, в отличие от других блокчейнов, возможности Эфириума гораздо шире. Эфириум программируется, это означает, что разработчики могут использовать его для создания новых видов приложений.
 Эти децентрализованные приложения (dapps) совмещают в себе преимущества криптовалюты и технологию блокчейна. Им можно доверять, поскольку после того, как они будут загружены в Эфириум, они всегда будут работать так, как это было запрограммировано. Они могут работать с цифровыми активами для создания новых видов финансовых приложений. Они могут быть децентрализованы, что означает, что ни одна организация и ни одно конкретное лицо не смогут контролировать их.
 В данный момент тысячи разработчиков во всем мире создают приложения на Эфириуме."

playstore_details.title: MEW wallet – Ethereum wallet
playstore_details.description:
This is an official mobile app for MyEtherWallet, Ethereum's original and most trusted wallet.

Get from zero to crypto. Fast and safe.

Main features:
* Buy crypto with a few taps using your bank card
* Create an Ethereum wallet
* Hold and send Ether and tokens
* Swap, Exchange and Trade Ether, and ERC-20 tokens
* Ethereum 2.0 staking: stake Ether on Eth2 chain.
* Learn about Ethereum, Blockchain, safety and security.
* Send and receive Ether and ERC-20 tokens
* Easily interact with multiple accounts for privacy and convenience
* Connect to MEW web, via myetherwallet.com, and use all of its extended features.

BUY CRYPTO WITH JUST A FEW TAPS
Buy Ether right inside MEW wallet using your bank card

OWN YOUR FUNDS: YOU ARE IN FULL CONTROL
MEW wallet is a true, non-custodial Ethereum wallet. This means that you and only you have access to your funds.

SUPPORTING ALL ERC-20 TOKENS
If it is on Ethereum blockchain MEW wallet will support it. No need to add custom tokens manually.

STAY SAFE, MEW'S GOT YOUR BACK
— We will teach you how to stay safe and secure in the world of crypto.

— We keep your account secure by using state of the art encryption and storing your keys localy in a secure vault on your device.

— We help you backup your wallet so you can recover your funds in case your device gets lost or stolen.

MULTIPLE ACCOUNTS
Use as many accounts as you like and fluidily switch between all of them, for privacy and convenience.

ALL THE POWER OF MEW WEB
Connect to MyEtherWallet.com, to use all of its extended features, while safely keeping your keys on your mobile device.

Features available when connected to MEW web: 
— Swap & trade
— Sign messages 
— Convert crypto back to Fiat
— Register ENS names
— Interact with DApps
— Deploy and interact with smart contracts

Your keys are safely stored in a local secure enclave.
